      "title": "¡Bienvenido!",
      "content": {
        "subtitle": "Lección 1 · A1",
        "body": "In this lesson you'll learn the most common Spanish greetings and polite expressions. ¡Vamos!"
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 20 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c2",
      "type": "VocabularyCard",
      "content": {
        "word": "Hola",
        "nativeTranslation": "Hola",
        "englishTranslation": "Hello / Hi",
        "pronunciation": "OH-lah",
        "ipa": "ola",
        "partOfSpeech": "interjection",
        "difficulty": "easy",
        "exampleSentence": "¡Hola! ¿Cómo estás?",
        "nativeExample": "Hi! How are you?",
        "audio": { "key": "es/a1/hola.mp3" }
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 30 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c3",
      "type": "VocabularyCard",
      "content": {
        "word": "Gracias",
        "nativeTranslation": "Gracias",
        "englishTranslation": "Thank you",
        "pronunciation": "GRAH-syas",
        "ipa": "ˈɡɾasjas",
        "partOfSpeech": "interjection",
        "difficulty": "easy",
        "exampleSentence": "¡Muchas gracias!",
        "nativeExample": "Thank you very much!",
        "audio": { "key": "es/a1/gracias.mp3" }
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 30 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c4",
      "type": "InfoCard",
      "title": "Morning vs. evening",
      "content": {
        "tone": "tip",
        "body": "Use \"Buenos días\" in the morning, \"Buenas tardes\" in the afternoon, and \"Buenas noches\" at night. \"Hola\" works any time!"
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 25 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c5",
      "type": "FlashCard",
